This paper focuses on analyzing language usage and patterns across demographic groups in Twitter, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of image processing algorithms to extract demographic information also suggests a potential overlap with computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis of topics of interest could also fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or data mining (cs.SD). Finally, the study of linguistic diversity and demographic differences in online communication could be relevant to cyberpsychology (cs.CY) or social and economic networks (cs.SOC).
